# Fetal Health Classification
I built this project while learning more about machine learning and data analysis. I wanted to understand how classification models work on real medical data and how different features can affect predictions.
The project focuses on classifying fetal health into three categories using Cardiotocography (CTG) exam data: Normal, Suspect, and Pathological.
While working on this project, I learned how to explore datasets, analyze relationships between features, improve model performance, and evaluate models properly instead of only focusing on accuracy.
I also practiced using tools like GridSearchCV and cross validation to better understand how machine learning models are tuned and tested.
For the project, I performed Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), created correlation heatmaps and scatter plots, selected important features based on correlation, and applied hyperparameter tuning with 5-Fold Cross Validation.
Tech stack used in this project includes Python, Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, and Seaborn.
Dataset source: Kaggle — Fetal Health Classification
